gomodel:SYNGO_4645  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Although many figures in this paper focus on postsynaptic localization of Bin1, there is also immunogold EM evidence for presynaptic localization of Bin1 in mouse cortex as shown in Figures 1h and S1c.. Experimental description: \"Immuno-electron microscopy (immuno-EM)\n\nThe basic approach is as described in [34]. Deeply-anesthetized adult C57/BL6 mice were perfused with mixed aldehyde fixative; brains were removed, post-fixed overnight in the same fixative, and stored in pH 7.2 phosphate buffer.\"\n\nAntibodies;\nBin1 mAb (Millipore Cat# 05-449)\nGluA1 N-term mAb (Millipore Cat# MAB2263)\nGluA1 C-term pAb (Millipore Cat# ABN241)\nSynapsin mAb (CellSignaling Cat# 5297)\nPSD95 mAb (Neuromab Cat# 75-028)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4645" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

